headline.main: PEACE BID TO SOVIET SEEN; Hitler-Schulenburg Talk Held Basis of Rumor in Stockholm

lead_paragraph: STOCKHOLM, Sweden, March 1 -- Reports were current in Stockholm tonight that the visit to Reichsfuehrer Hitler's headquarters of Count Fredrich Werner von der Schulenburg, former German Ambassador to Moscow, was connected with the possibility of an offer of peace to Russia.
abstract: Count von der Schulenberg and Hitler conf linked to new German peace bid to USSR
